Explanation:

We use a dynamic programming approach to solve the problem. We create a 2D array (dp) with dimensions (n+1)x(m+1), where n is the length of string s and m is the length of string pattern. We iterate through the strings s and pattern to fill the dp array. If the characters at positions i-1 in s and j-1 in pattern are equal, we set dp[i][j] to j. Otherwise, we find the minimum of the three following values: dp[i-1][j], dp[i][j-1], and dp[i-1][j-1].

Finally, we return the value at dp[n][m], which represents the minimum number of changes needed to make s[i] and pattern[j] equal.

